[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cloverhill Prison stand-off: Eleven inmates taken to hospital after riot

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Eleven prisoners have been taken to hospital after a stand-off by inmates at Cloverhill Prison in Dublin.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident has ended, but two inmates remain on the roof of the prison and have caused significant damage, according to prison authorities.
The stand-off began when 60 prisoners refused to leave an exercise yard.
Forty-five returned to their cells, but 15 armed themselves with homemade weapons and fought with prison officers.
Prison officers with riot shields and batons moved in and forcibly returned the inmates to their cells.
One inmate, who was taken hostage by other prisoners, was attacked and sustained a broken arm.
Eleven prisoners have been taken to Dublin's Tallaght hospital.
Two other inmates climbed onto the prison roof.
Prison authorities are working to bring the prisoners down.
